queries.queryString:
_index=sumologic_volume _sourceCategory = "sourcecategory_and_tier_volume"
| parse regex "(?<data>\{[^\{]+\})" multi
| json field=data "field","dataTier" as sourcecategory, dataTier
| where dataTier matches "{{Tier}}"
| where !isEmpty(sourcecategory)
| if ("{{Filter}}"="*", "*", concat("*", toLowerCase("{{Filter}}"), "*")) as filter
| where toLowerCase(sourcecategory) matches filter
| count by sourcecategory
| sort sourcecategory asc
| fields -_count

This dashboard does NOT take your Role Search Filter into consideration. It uses the data volume index to display the built-in metadata fields available across all data in Sumo. You can use the filter above to see which data is available to based on Data Tier.
See [Sumo Built-In Metadata](https://help-opensource.sumologic.com/docs/search/get-started-with-search/search-basics/built-in-metadata/) for more details.
